ES is a 

    1) Real-time distributed search
    2) Real-time analytics
    3) Distributed



It allows:
    1) full-text search
    2) 

GitHub uses ES to query 130 billions lines of code
Wikipedia/Stack Overflow / Guardian all use it


run on your laptop, or scale out to hundreds of servers and petabytes of data

No individual part of Elasticsearch is new or revolutionary. Full-text search has been done before, as have analytics systems and distributed databases.


